<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-09-07T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-09-07T16:00:00-05:00" n="369" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d369">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">862S.01/5: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Whitlock</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-09-07T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September 7,
                                        1921—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>39. Herrick has been instructed to repeat to you Department’s memorandum
                            on A and B mandates.<note n="2" xml:id="d369fn2">For text of memorandum,
                                see telegram no. 377, Aug. 7, 1921, to the Ambassador in France,
                                    <ref target="frus1921v01#pg_922"><hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>,
                                    vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 922</ref>.</note> On
                            receipt of his telegram please transmit immediately to Foreign Office
                            for its information text of memorandum.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>